 🖌️ Etch-a-Sketch with Python Turtle

This is a simple Etch-a-Sketch-style drawing program made using Python's built-in Turtle graphics module. 
You can control the turtle with your keyboard to draw lines, turn directions, and clear the screen just like a classic Etch-a-Sketch toy.

🚀 Features

- Move the turtle forward and backward
- Turn left or right
- Clear the screen and reset the turtle's position
- Real-time drawing with keyboard input

🎮 Controls

| Key | Action                        |
|-----|-------------------------------|
| `W` | Move turtle forward           |
| `S` | Move turtle backward          |
| `A` | Turn turtle left              |
| `D` | Turn turtle right             |
| `C` | Clear the screen and reset    |


